schms-drawing-data-structures-parity — support SCHMS XData, dictionaries, XRecords and tables
================================================================================================

Context
-------

The initial SCHMS non-regression corpus covers not only graphical entities but
also drawing-resident data: registered applications and XData, dictionaries,
XRecords, symbol tables and selected system variables.  The same scenarios
must run headlessly in clautolisp and in AutoCAD/BricsCAD.

The long-term architecture is tracked by `drawing-database-api.issue`.  This
issue defines the minimum observable AutoLISP surface required by the first
SCHMS test tranche.

Required subset
---------------

Inventory the exact SCHMS calls and complete the necessary behaviour for:

  - REGAPP records and XData read/write through ENTGET/ENTMOD;
  - NAMEDOBJDICT, DICTADD, DICTSEARCH, DICTNEXT and DICTREMOVE;
  - XRECORD creation, mutation, enumeration and deletion;
  - TBLSEARCH, TBLNEXT and TBLobjNAME for layers, linetypes, blocks and any
    other table selected by the SCHMS inventory;
  - GETVAR/SETVAR for the batch scenarios' drawing-scoped variables;
  - ownership/reactor group codes needed to preserve these structures.

Semantics and fidelity
----------------------

Preserve group multiplicity and meaningful ordering inside XData and XRecords.
Do not normalize data in the host merely to make snapshot comparison easier;
normalization belongs to the SCHMS test helper.  Match vendor nil/error and
duplicate-name behaviour using portable probes.

Acceptance
----------

  - A portable scenario creates, reads, updates and removes an XData payload.
  - A portable scenario performs the same lifecycle for a dictionary/XRecord.
  - Required symbol-table records can be created or discovered and enumerated
    with vendor-compatible results.
  - Drawing-scoped system variables used by the corpus are isolated between
    fresh test sessions.
  - Snapshot-visible values match AutoCAD and BricsCAD after normalization.
  - Missing structures fail or return nil as the selected CAD dialect does;
    no Common Lisp condition leaks into AutoLISP.
  - Existing suites remain green on SBCL and CCL.

Out of scope
------------

DWG/DXF persistence, COM/ObjectDBX, multi-document lifecycle, UI state and
rendering.


SCHMS call inventory (recorded 2026-07-24)
------------------------------------------
The SCHMS+ AutoLISP call inventory is committed at
issues/open/schms-call-inventory.md (acceptance item #1). It calibrates
ordering/priority; per pjb the implementation targets the FULL AutoLISP
spec + AutoCAD/BricsCAD reference, not only the SCHMS subset.


STATUS (2026-07-24, branch schms-data-selection, clautolisp 1.6.8+)
===================================================================
Headless core: DONE.   Vendor verification: BLOCKED on live CAD access.

Implemented (headless, green now)
---------------------------------
- REGAPP: real builtin (was an M6 nil-stub). Registers an APPID record;
  returns the app name, or nil when already registered or when the name
  fails SNVALID. host-regapp on the mock host; register-appid /
  appid-registered-p in the drawing model.
- XData read/write through ENTGET/ENTMOD across the FULL group-code set
  (1000 string, 1001 appname, 1002 control {/} incl. nesting, 1003 layer,
  1004 binary, 1005 handle, 1010/1011/1012/1013 points, 1040 real,
  1041/1042 dist/scale, 1070 int16, 1071 int32). Order and multiplicity
  preserved verbatim (the host never normalizes). ENTMOD edits xdata per
  application (replace/remove/leave-untouched). ENTGET applist filtering
  incl. multi-application lists and the "*" wildcard.
- Named-object dictionary tree: NAMEDOBJDICT, DICTADD, DICTSEARCH,
  DICTNEXT, DICTREMOVE, DICTRENAME, DICTOBJNAME — real builtins (were
  M6 stubs). Duplicate-key DICTADD -> nil; absent-key DICTSEARCH -> nil;
  no CL condition leaks. Sub-dictionary trees supported.
- XRECORD objects: created with ENTMAKEX, mutated with ENTMOD, read via
  DICTSEARCH/DICTNEXT (entget-style (-1 . ename)-headed list), deleted
  via ENTDEL, detached via DICTREMOVE; ordered group codes preserved.
- Symbol tables: TBLSEARCH/TBLNEXT/TBLOBJNAME over the FULL standard set
  — LAYER, LTYPE(=LINETYPE), STYLE(=TEXTSTYLE), BLOCK(=block-record),
  VIEW, UCS, VPORT, DIMSTYLE, APPID. FIX: table record string values are
  now AutoLISP-wrapped (strcat/=/type accept them; previously raw CL
  strings that those operators rejected — a latent foundation defect,
  fixed here as part of table parity).
- GETVAR/SETVAR isolation: each fresh MockHost owns a fresh drawing, so
  drawing-scoped sysvars (and dictionaries, entities) do not leak between
  sessions. Regression test dictionaries-are-isolated-between-fresh-hosts.
- Ownership group codes: DICTADD stamps the member's owner (330) to the
  dictionary; dictionaries carry 330 owner + 3/350 entry pairs.

Model/representation decision (DICT-1)
--------------------------------------
Dictionaries and xrecords are stored as handle-bearing objects in the
ENTITIES table (drawing/source/dictionary.lisp), so their enames feed
straight into ENTGET/ENTMOD/ENTDEL with no parallel code path. ssget
excludes non-graphical objects (graphical-entity-p), matching the vendor.
Divergence to verify on CAD: ENTNEXT/ENTLAST can enumerate these objects
here, whereas AutoCAD confines them to the OBJECTS section. Filed as
entnext-nongraphical-enumeration.issue.

Deferred (filed separately)
---------------------------
- Creating symbol-table records from AutoLISP via ENTMAKE (LAYER/LTYPE/
  STYLE/BLOCK): today only APPID grows (via REGAPP); an ENTMAKE of a
  table record is stored as an object, not a table row. See
  entmake-symbol-table-records.issue.
- XDROOM / XDSIZE (xdata room/size queries) remain nil M6 stubs — the
  in-memory model does not bound xdata storage. See
  xdroom-xdsize-not-implemented.issue.

